In this paper, we have studied the basic reproduction number in stochastic epidemic models to include random perturbations in the infection rate as the contributing factor for the spread of the epidemics. We have established stability conditions for the SIS, SIR, and SEIR epidemic models. As in the case of the deterministic SEIR model, the condition \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
